of me. I could not breathe. Then I heard someone say ` my vice president', and he and others picked me up and took me inside a store.'' The man who picked him up, <PERSON> Gilberto </PERSON> <PERSON> Cardenas </PERSON>, said he and others also picked up <PERSON> Endara </PERSON> and put him in a truck to take him to a hospital. The Dignity Battalion is made up of civilians recruited into armed groups with the expressed purpose of defending <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> in case of a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> invasion, which <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> has been saying could happen. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forces </ORGANIZATION>, has been de facto leader of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> since 1983. `` The world knows ... that what's at stake here is not <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Canal </LOCATION> -LRB- as the government claims -RRB- but the desire of a people to be free,'' said <PERSON> Arias </PERSON> <PERSON> Calderon </PERSON>.
