<HEAD>Four Professors Leaving English Faculty; Alleged Sexual Incident
Cited</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TOM KRATTENMAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Princeton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>'s English department says his recent resignation was prompted in part by lenient treatment of a professor accused of making sexual advances on a student <PERSON> Emory </PERSON> <PERSON> Elliott </PERSON> is one of four members of the English faculty to resign since a controversy erupted over the September incident, which involved a male English professor and a male graduate student. The professor, <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> McFarland </PERSON>, 62, was suspended that month for one year. Faculty members had hoped he would be eased out altogether, <PERSON> Elliott </PERSON> said. The student who allegedly was the target of the advance reported it to police last week, but it was unclear if charges would be filed. <PERSON> Kim </PERSON> <PERSON> Otis </PERSON>, a lawyer representing the student, said his client told police it was a `` criminal assault of a sexual nature'' but denied the student was alleging rape or sexual assault. <PERSON> Otis </PERSON> said there was a `` definite reason'' the student did not go to police sooner, but the attorney refused to elaborate. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Wills </PERSON>, <PERSON> McFarland </PERSON>'s lawyer, said the student's delay cast doubt on his allegations. University officials have refused to comment on <PERSON> McFarland </PERSON>'s suspension or on the alleged incident The Princetonian, the student newspaper, reported that the episode occurred after an English department party. <PERSON> Elliott </PERSON>, who is leaving for the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Riverside </LOCATION>, said his disillusionment with the <ORGANIZATION> Ivy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> school's administration mounted after it notified the faculty in January it would allow <PERSON> McFarland </PERSON> to re