<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Prime Minister <PERSON> Noboru </PERSON> <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> met senior statesman <PERSON> Masayoshi </PERSON> <PERSON> Ito </PERSON> today but failed to persuade the reform-minded politician to succeed him when he steps down over an influence-peddling scandal, sources said. Local news reports said <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> and <PERSON> Ito </PERSON>, a former foreign minister, are at odds over <PERSON> Ito </PERSON>'s call for an end to party factions. <PERSON> Ito </PERSON>, in naming his terms for leading the scandal-tainted party and becoming <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s next prime minister, also has demanded the resignations of all party officials connected to corruption cases. After meeting more than three hours today, the two <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leaders said their discussions focused on reform of the party, whose popular support has been deeply eroded by the so-called Recruit scandal. `` My feeling has not changed,'' <PERSON> Ito </PERSON> said. `` I believe Mr. <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> has n't got a good impression'' of the conditions under which he would accept the country's top post. Though <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> was expected to ask <PERSON> Ito </PERSON> to accept the party presidency, he told reporters after the meeting: `` We entered today's talks after confirming between each other that I'm not in a position to make any request today.'' <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> leads the largest of six major factions that make up the <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>. Balancing factional strength is an important factor in determining appointments to the Cabinet and has become a widely accepted feature of the ruling party organization. Political fundraising _ a key issue in the current scandal _ is a major part of factional competition. The discredited prime mini