<DATELINE>VANDENBERG AIR FORCE BASE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An unarmed Midgetman missile went off course and was destroyed today during the first test flight of the controversial weapon system, the program director said. The missile began to tumble about 70 seconds into the flight while its second stage was firing and the range safety officer issued a destruct command, Maj. Gen. <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> told reporters. But he called the launch a `` qualified success'' because the flight test met about 50 percent of its objectives. The intercontinental ballistic missile, designed to be fired from a truck launcher, blasted off from a concrete pad at 11 a.m. PDT. The missile was supposed to deliver a dummy warhead to a test range about 4,600 miles away in the <LOCATION> Kwajalein </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Atoll </LOCATION>. The Midgetman, formally the Small Intercontinental Ballistic Missile, is designed to carry a single nuclear warhead to a target up to 6,900 miles away. The three-stage missile weighs 37,000 pounds, stands about 52 feet tall and is 46 inches in diameter. The weapon is at the center of a controversy over whether the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> should develop one or two mobile nuclear missiles to deter the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> from attempting a first strike against missiles inside silos. The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> has deployed two such `` land-mobile'' missiles, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> none. <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Cheney </PERSON> would prefer to develop only one _ a version of the huge, 10-warhead MX that could be carried and launched from a rail car. Democratic leaders on Capitol Hill prefer the smaller, more mobile Midgetman. President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> recently decided, however, to pursue development of both the MX and Midgetman. The major contractors on the Midgetman include <ORG