million the 25,000-student university received in grants during 1988 came from the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Quakers </ORGANIZATION> said they will appeal the board's decision to the state <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Quality </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Engineering </ORGANIZATION>. They have also placed an article before town meeting that would ban all military-funded research at <LOCATION> Amherst </LOCATION>. The town will vote on that question in late May or early June.
