<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Convicted stock brokerage founder <PERSON> Boyd </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Jefferies </PERSON> testified he engaged in four unlawful stock deals with corporate takeover strategist <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bilzerian </PERSON>. Testifying at <PERSON> Bilzerian </PERSON>'s securities fraud trial at federal court in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> on Wednesday, <PERSON> Jefferies </PERSON>, who said he only met the <ORGANIZATION> Singer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> chairman once, detailed their dealings in four stock transactions in 1985 and 1986. The indictment alleges that <ORGANIZATION> Jefferies </ORGANIZATION> secretly held stock for <PERSON> Bilzerian </PERSON> in four deals involving <ORGANIZATION> Cluett </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peabody </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Hammerhill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Paper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, H.H. <ORGANIZATION> Robertson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Armco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The federal bankruptcy court extended a bidding deadline on <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> for at least one potential suitor, as a bidder for <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s profitable <ORGANIZATION> Northeast </ORGANIZATION> shuttle raised its offer for that business. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Judge <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON> extended the Wednesday deadline for an investor group led by <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Ritchie </PERSON>, a prominent <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> commodities trader, to give it more time to receive financial information from Eastern.
